    <entry>
      <title>The Ultimate Secret From Sage</title>
      <link href="/2020/07/20/caprice/the_ultimate_secret_from_sage/"/>
      <url>/2020/07/20/caprice/the_ultimate_secret_from_sage/</url>
      
        <content type="html"><![CDATA[<blockquote><p>Cultivate myself, towards a better and more rational person… It’s a life-long persuit!<br><a id="more"></a></p><p>Think about the quote over and over again, do frequent retrospection and think about what’s the next step.</p></blockquote><figure class="highlight plain"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br><span class="line">5</span><br><span class="line">6</span><br><span class="line">7</span><br><span class="line">8</span><br><span class="line">9</span><br><span class="line">10</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t have a lot of envy.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t have a lot of resentment.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You don&#39;t overspend your income.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You stay cheerful in spite of your troubles.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;You deal with reliable people.&quot;</span><br><span class="line">&quot;And you do what you&#39;re supposed to do.&quot;</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">And all these simple rules work so well to make your life better. And they&#39;re so trit</span><br><span class="line"></span><br><span class="line">- Charlie Munger</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p>Just love it, I think this quote is “the ultimate secret” behind happiness. </p>]]></content>
      
      
      
